==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Prelacy
<hw>Prel"a*cy</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>; <plu><it>pl.</it>
<plw>Prelacies</plw> <pr>(#)</pr>.</plu> <ety>[LL. <ets>praelatia</ets>.
See <er>Prelate</er>; cf. <er>Prelaty</er>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>The
office or dignity of a prelate; church government by prelates.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Prelacies may be termed the greater benefices.</q>
<rj><qau>Ayliffe.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>The order of prelates, taken collectively; the body
of ecclesiastical dignitaries.</def> ⟦ldquo⟧Divers of the reverend
<xex>prelacy</xex>, and other most judicious men.⟦rdquo⟧
<rj><au>Hooker.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Prelal</ent>⟦br⟧
